; =============================================================================
; LMHOSTS - KSDOS NetBIOS Name Resolution
; NetBIOS over TCP/IP name resolution file
; =============================================================================

# Copyright (c) 1993-1999 Microsoft Corp.
#
# This is a sample LMHOSTS file used by the Microsoft TCP/IP for Windows.
#
# This file contains the mappings of IP addresses to computer names
# (NetBIOS names) or NetBIOS scope. Each entry should be kept on an
# individual line. The IP address should be placed in the first column
# followed by the corresponding computer name. The computer name
# and NetBIOS scope should be separated by a backslash "\" as
# in the following example:
#
#      102.54.94.97     production     # Production server
#      102.54.94.98     sales          # Sales server
#      102.54.94.99     backup         # Backup server
#
# Additionally, comments (such as these) may be inserted on individual
# lines or following the computer name denoted by a '#' symbol.
#
# For example:
#
#      102.54.94.97     rhino.acme.com          # source server
#      102.54.94.102    rhino.acme.com          # destination server
#
# The following example illustrates an additional use for LMHOSTS:
#
#      102.54.94.102     prod                 # Special name for PROD server
#      102.54.94.123     sales                # Special name for SALES server
#
# By default, this file should be placed in the C:\WINDOWS directory.

# KSDOS NetBIOS names
127.0.0.1       KSDOS
127.0.0.1       KERNEL
127.0.0.1       SERVICES
127.0.0.1       AUTH

# Predefined entries for KSDOS development
# 192.168.1.10    SERVER1
# 192.168.1.11    WORKSTATION1
# 192.168.1.12    WORKSTATION2

# Include statement for centralized LMHOSTS file
# INCLUDE \\SERVER\SHARE\LMHOSTS
